org.chronos.chronodb.internal.api.cache

Interface ChronoDBCache

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    ChronoDBBogusCache, MosaicCache

    public interface ChronoDBCache
    The ChronoDBCache is responsible for caching GetResults.

    This helps to reduce accesses to the underlying store, which in turn reduces the need for I/O operations.

    • Nested Class Summary

      Nested Classes 
      Modifier and Type Interface and Description
      static interface  ChronoDBCache.CacheStatistics
      This interface describes a set of statistics that can be retrieved about a ChronoDBCache.

        Creates a new cache according to the settings in the given configuration.
        Parameters:
        config - The configuration to read the cache settings from. Must not be null.
        Returns:
        A cache instance matching the given configuration. Never null.

        Parameters:
        branch - The branch to search in. Must not be null.
        timestamp - The timestamp to search at. Must not be null.
        qualifiedKey - The qualified key to search for. Must not be null.
        Returns:

      • cache

        void cache(java.lang.String branch,
           GetResult<?> queryResult)
        Adds the given GetResult to this cache.
        Parameters:
        branch - The branch that was requested. Must not be null.

      • writeThrough

        void writeThrough(java.lang.String branch,
                  long timestamp,
                  QualifiedKey key,
                  java.lang.Object value)
        Writes the given key-value pair through the cache.

        This is similar to cache(String, GetResult), except that this method works directly on the value object instead of a GetResult.

        This method assumes that the validity period of the given key-value pair is open-ended at the righthand side.

        Parameters:
        branch - The branch of the entry to write through the cache.
        timestamp - The timestamp of the entry to write through the cache.
        key - The qualified key of the key-value pair
        value - The value of the key-value pair

      • size

        int size()
        Retrieves the current number of entries in the cache.
        Returns:
        The current size of the cache. Never negative, may be zero.

      • getStatistics

        ChronoDBCache.CacheStatistics getStatistics()
        Returns the statistics of this cache.

        This method will return a copy of the statistics. Any modifications on the cache (including resetStatistics()) will have no influence on the returned statistics object.

        Returns:
        A copy of the statistics. Never null.

      • resetStatistics

        void resetStatistics()
        Resets the statistics of this cache.

      • rollbackToTimestamp

        void rollbackToTimestamp(long timestamp)
        Rolls the cache back to the specified timestamp, i.e. removes all entries that are newer than the specified timestamp.
        Parameters:

      • writeThrough

        default void writeThrough(java.lang.String branch,
                          long timestamp,
                          java.util.Map<QualifiedKey,java.lang.Object> keyValues)
        Writes the given map of key-value pairs through this cache i.e. adds all entries to the cache.

        This method assumes that the validity range of all pairs is open-ended on the righthand side.

        Parameters:
        branch - The branch to associate the entries with. Must not be null.
        timestamp - The timestamp to associate the entries with. Must not be null.
        keyValues - The key-value pairs to write through the cache. May be empty, but must not be null.
